<br>
For me, I took the hint.  I stayed guildless, went and worked on my aa's (pre-pop they were a bitch lol), worked on a few quests to improve my character, stayed off the message boards almost completely, and most important, stayed in touch with ADers and got good advice on improving in the future.  My advice to you if you really want to be in AD with all your gnome heart, is to do the same.  Keep working on your aa's, do quests with your friends, and stay in touch with the AD warriors to improve your progress.  The other day you posted a poem on the MiM message board and said something like the people over at AD won't let me do this (sounded negative toward AD), you can't do that if you want to be a part of them.  It sounds very resentful and who would want that in a guildmate.  Anyway, that's my advice - take it or leave it. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~nmenasch/kyle.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
