<br>
It's all about attitude , cooperation, and dedication.<br>
<br>
I'll break it down.<br>
<br>
&quot;Attitude&quot; - getting along with the rest of AD, and not causing problems because of inability to respect others outside the guild. not being arrogant.<br>
<br>
&quot;Cooperation&quot; - willingness to work together to achieve a common goal. Common goal #1,234,095 = slay monster #1,234,095, this goal was probably the same as common goal #1, which was to slay monster #1(I dont just mean boss mobs, I mean every single monster along the way, because without cooperation, you wont be killing a single mob if your clerics are not in touch with your warriors.) The more cooperation there is, the faster these mobs will die, and you won't have to sit thru corpse recovery #1,059, buying small coffin #624. And listen to your raid leaders, whoever is in charge at the time. <br>
<br>
&quot;Dedication&quot; - the amount of energy and time you sacrifice for the sake of yourself and your guild. Because we all know by improving yourself, you are improving the guild in a small way. Everyone benefits from everyone elses achievements within a guild. Dedication is also seen from helping others. Not just yourself. By helping others who are having a more difficult time, or who just need a cleric or a tank or an enchanter or whatever they need, will help the guild too. When I say that improving yourself improves the guild, that goes for everyone.<br>
<br>
Combining these three things will create the key that opens the door to AD.(ok, so I've played too much EQ)<br>
<br>
Now, get out your pen and check off what you what you think you have achieved. Whatever is left unchecked is up to you to solve. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aybolit>Aybolit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#333333>(2/1/03 4:04 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Somthor</span><hr size=1> That's a shame. Somthor is one of very few genially good natured people I've met on this server. I would not call him my friend but I always wanted him to succeed <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://p075.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm5.showMessageRange?topicID=357.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://p075.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm5.showMessageRange?topicID=357.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://p075.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm5.showMessageRange?topicID=357.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a> <b>4</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://p075.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm5.showPrevMessage?topicID=357.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://p075.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm5.showNextMessage?topicID=357.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://p075.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm5.threadControl?topicID=357.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://p075.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm5.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=357.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 he